\pard\f0\fs28   Extremely variable; of the more widespread variants{\b  P. oxyptera} Reichenb., {\i Pl. Crit. }{\b 1}: 25 (1823), seems to have the strongest claim for recognition at specific rank; it is distinguished by the lanceolate to lanceolate-elliptical, acute wings, never wider than the capsule. It appears, however, that although in some regions (e.g. Poland) it is constant and readily distinguishable, in others (e.g. Britain) it is not.
