\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 28. P. cristagalli} Chodat, {\i Bull. Soc. Bot. Genève} ser. 2, {\b 5}: 110 (1913). Stems 15-20 cm, flexuous. Leaves glabrescent, acute, the lower broadly lanceolate, the upper linear-lanceolate. Racemes 1-2 cm, terminal on main axis and on upper axillary branches, forming a corymbose panicle. Outer sepals 3 mm, subulate; wings 5 × 1·5 mm, lanceolate, apiculate; veins not anastomosing. Crest of keel with long, narrow lobes. Capsule ¾ as long as wings. Seeds oblong-ellipsoid; lobes of strophiole flattened, erect, forming an apical crest. •{\i  S. Greece.} Gr.
