\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 29. P. edmundii} Chodat,{\i  Bull. Herb. Boiss. }{\b 4}: 911 (1896). Stems c. 5 cm, numerous, slender, woody at the base. Leaves glabrous, increasing in size upwards, the lower 2-4 mm, spathulate, obtuse, opposite, the upper up to 10 mm, elliptical, obtuse, alternate, forming a small rosette below the raceme. Racemes terminal, sessile, very short, corymbose. wings c. 5 mm, ovate, shortly clawed; veins anastomosing. Corolla-tube short; upper petals oblong, obtuse. •{\i  N.W. Spain} ({\i Picos de Europa}). Hs.
